snippet: Iranian oil shipments to foreign customers increased in February, a report said Wednesday, despite a new regimen of American sanctions over Iran’s disputed nuclear program.
abstract: International Energy Agency reports that Iranian oil shipments to foreign customers increased in Feb 2013 despite new regimen of American sanctions over country's nuclear program.
lead_paragraph: Iranian oil shipments to foreign customers increased in February, a report said Wednesday, despite a new regimen of American sanctions over Iran’s disputed nuclear program.

headline.main: Iran: Oil Exports Rose, Report Says
